						<div class="story-body">
								<p>I&#8217;ve been one of the folks running out Best Literary Film Adaptation bracket this week—<a href="https://lithub.com/what-is-the-best-literary-film-adaptation-of-the-last-50-years-day-five/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">have you voted yet?</a>—and so I&#8217;ve missed a few of this week&#8217;s stories. Let&#8217;s catch up together with some Venns.</p>
<p>This is a sidebar, but there&#8217;s a joke about the former Prime Minister of Canada below, and it would be irresponsible of me to not share this clip of a young Trudeau showing off his &#8220;party trick&#8221; of <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y2mrFBLzuIs" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">throwing himself down the stairs.</a> It&#8217;s true what they say: all politics is local and sometimes local is at the bottom of the stairs.</p>
<p>Hope you get to showcase your party trick this weekend, and I&#8217;ll see you back here on Monday!</p>
